{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f201040b-3c1d-402b-9ba1-04733c7401ba","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2**, which supports the modern approach. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncDisposable\n{\n    // TestContext is injected via constructor in MSTest 3.x\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; }\n\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        TestContext = testContext;\n        // Synchronous initialization here\n    }\n\n    // Async initialization via IAsyncInitialization (or use [TestInitialize])\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // Async per-test setup\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public async Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        // Async per-test teardown\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    // Async disposal via IAsyncDisposable\n    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync()\n    {\n        // Async class-level teardown\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        TestContext.WriteLine(\"Running test\");\n        Assert.IsTrue(true);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points for MSTest 3.x:**\n\n- **Constructor injection** — `TestContext` is passed via constructor (no more `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property magic).\n- **Sync init** — use the constructor.\n- **Async init** — use `[TestInitialize]` (per-test) or `[ClassInitialize]` (per-class, must be `static`).\n- **Async cleanup** — implement `IAsyncDisposable` and/or use `[TestCleanup]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"205ad81e-4f84-4c80-9199-233d8a83375b","outputTokens":439,"requestId":"1055:1DB847:2E962A0:33A3E85:6A02ED04"},"id":"fc120be5-d6cf-4bd1-8510-aaca9a26c1b1","timestamp":"2026-05-12T09:04:21.113Z","parentId":"a8b36436-1928-4d5c-9c57-fe9377c9d8dd"}
